President Jacob Zuma says there are those in South Africa who robbed others of their possessions.CAPE TOWN &#8211; President Jacob Zuma says he&#8217;s not a racist and he does not hate white people.Responding to the Freedom Front Plus&#8217; Pieter Groenewald during his reply to his budget vote in the National Assembly on Thursday afternoon, Zuma said as a child of the African National Congress he was taught non-racialism.But he says this does not mean he shouldn&#8217;t correct the wrongs in South Africa.Zuma says he believes in reconciliation and putting the past behind him. But there is a reality in SA that between us there are those who have robbed others of their own possessions and made it theirs and left others to be poor. 